I have structured the solution in eight views.
First, I define the business context and desired outcomes.
Then I explain the target architecture and end-to-end flow.
After that, I isolate the decision engine because in banking the logic, risk scoring, and explainability need separate attention.
I then cover non-functional requirements and governance to show how the solution will scale and remain controlled in production.
Finally, I present risks, trade-offs, and a phased roadmap so stakeholders can see both the target state and the path to get there.
